## HOW THE TEMPLATE RENDERS (automatic, no config needed)

Given a post with the right frontmatter, `ShopTemplate.tsx` automatically:

1. Renders `InlineNewsletter` at top
2. Renders hero (category label, H1 title, author, date, read time, hero image)
3. Renders `Breadcrumbs` → Shop > Post Title
4. Renders mobile TOC (hidden on desktop)
5. If `winnerIndex` set → renders `WinnerBadge` (the top pick, below hero)
6. Splits content into 3 sections (30% / 30% / 40%)
7. Renders first section
8. If `winnerIndex` set → renders `ShopInlineCTA` (mid-article strip)
9. Renders middle section
10. If `showComparison: true` → renders `ComparisonTable`
11. Renders remaining content
12. If `showProscons: true` → renders `ProsConsBlock` for each product
13. Renders second `InlineNewsletter`
14. Renders `ShopFinalCTA` (ranked list of top picks, winner highlighted)
15. If faqs exist → renders `ShopFAQ` accordion
16. Sticky desktop sidebar: TOC + winner product card with Shop Now CTA
17. Renders `AboutEEAT` + `FinalNewsletter` at bottom

