## RULES FOR WRITING SHOP POSTS

1. `winnerIndex` almost always set — it activates 3 components at once (WinnerBadge, InlineCTA, sidebar card)
2. `products[]` array is 0-indexed — `winnerIndex: 0` = first product in the list
3. `badge` on the winner product should match what you want displayed ("Best Overall", "Editor's Pick", etc.)
4. Inline product injection `{{PRODUCTS:n:i}}` works in both `.md` and `.mdx` files
5. `details[]` on a product = shown in WinnerBadge highlights + featured layout. Keep to 3 max for WinnerBadge.
6. `faqs` are always worth adding — they capture bottom-of-funnel search intent and improve SEO
7. `comparisonTable.columns[].values[]` must match `comparisonTable.features[]` length exactly
8. Use `true`/`false` for boolean features in comparison table (renders check/X), strings for text values
9. The `ShopFinalCTA` always renders if products exist — it auto-puts winner first regardless of order
10. Content body is standard markdown — H2 for main sections, H3 for sub-sections (TOC picks these up)

